<div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50">
  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="bg-red-900 text-white shadow-md">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-6 max-w-7xl flex justify-between items-center">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">QuickBooks Red Flag Detector</h1>
        <p class="text-red-100">Permissions Required</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-8 max-w-7xl">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="bg-red-100 border-l-4 border-red-600 p-6 mb-6">
        <div class="flex items-start">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0">
            <svg class="h-6 w-6 text-red-600" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div class="ml-4">
            <h3 class="text-lg leading-6 font-medium text-red-800">
              QuickBooks Permissions Required
            </h3>
            <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-red-700">
              <p><%= @error_message %></p>
              <% if @error_message && @error_message.include?("003100") %>
                <div class="mt-3 p-3 bg-yellow-100 border-l-2 border-yellow-500 text-xs text-yellow-900">
                  <p class="font-bold">Error 003100 Detected</p>
                  <p class="mt-1">This specific error indicates that one or more critical QuickBooks permissions are missing. When reconnecting, you MUST click "Yes" to ALL permission requests in the QuickBooks authorization screen.</p>
                </div>
              <% end %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Permission Issue Detected</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>Your QuickBooks account doesn't have the necessary permissions for Red Flag Detector to work correctly. This could be due to:</p>
        
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 my-4 text-gray-700">
          <li>Not authorizing all requested permissions during connection</li>
          <li>Your QuickBooks account type doesn't allow access to transaction data</li>
          <li>Your QuickBooks subscription level restricts API access</li>
          <li>Your authorization token has expired or been revoked</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-5 my-6">
          <div class="flex">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="h-5 w-5 text-yellow-500" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M18 10a8 8 0 11-16 0 8 8 0 0116 0zm-7-4a1 1 0 11-2 0 1 1 0 012 0zM9 9a1 1 0 000 2v3a1 1 0 001 1h1a1 1 0 100-2v-3a1 1 0 00-1-1H9z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div class="ml-3">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-yellow-800">CRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS - READ CAREFULLY</h3>
              
              <div class="mt-2 py-2 px-4 bg-red-50 border-l-2 border-red-400 text-red-800 font-bold mb-3">
                You MUST select "YES" to ALL permission requests in the QuickBooks authorization screen.
              </div>
              
              <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-yellow-700">
                <p>When reconnecting to QuickBooks:</p>
                <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 mt-2">
                  <li>Make sure you're logged into the QuickBooks account with administrative permissions</li>
                  <li>You <strong>MUST</strong> explicitly approve <strong>ALL</strong> permission scopes when prompted</li>
                  <li>Pay special attention to approving the <strong>Accounting</strong> scope which is essential</li>
                  <li>Also approve <strong>Profile</strong>, <strong>Email</strong> and <strong>OpenID</strong> scopes for user identification</li>
                  <li>Don't skip any permission requests or close the window prematurely</li>
                  <li>If you see "Read and write" permission requests, select <strong>YES</strong> to those as well</li>
                </ol>
              </div>
              
              <div class="mt-4 px-4 py-3 bg-blue-50 border-l-2 border-blue-400 text-blue-800">
                <p class="font-semibold">Important:</p>
                <p class="mt-1">Error 003100 typically occurs when your QuickBooks account has authorized our app, but hasn't granted all the required permissions. You must reconnect and approve <strong>ALL</strong> permission requests.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 mt-6">
          <a href="<%= quickbooks_disconnect_path %>" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-200 rounded-md text-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-300 transition inline-flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 16l4-4m0 0l-4-4m4 4H7m6 4v1a3 3 0 01-3 3H6a3 3 0 01-3-3V7a3 3 0 013-3h4a3 3 0 013 3v1" />
            </svg>
            Disconnect QuickBooks
          </a>
          <a href="<%= quickbooks_connect_path %>" class="px-6 py-3 bg-red-900 rounded-md text-white hover:bg-red-800 transition inline-flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
            </svg>
            Reconnect with Full Permissions
          </a>
          <a href="<%= root_path %>" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-800 rounded-md text-white hover:bg-gray-700 transition inline-flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 mr-2" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M3 12l2-2m0 0l7-7 7 7m-7-7v14" />
            </svg>
            Return to Home
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">About Required Permissions</h2>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>The Red Flag Detector needs access to the following QuickBooks data to function properly:</p>
        
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 my-4 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Accounting Data (Required)</strong> - For accessing bills, invoices, and transactions needed for red flag detection</li>
          <li><strong>OpenID, Profile, and Email (Required)</strong> - Basic user identity information for secure authentication</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p class="mb-3">We've simplified our permission requests to only include the essential scopes needed for basic functionality.</p>
        
        <div class="p-4 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-400 mb-4">
          <p><strong>Note:</strong> We use the most secure OAuth 2.0 connection method and never store your QuickBooks data between sessions. All analysis is performed temporarily during your session only.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer class="bg-gray-900 text-white py-6 mt-12">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-7xl text-center text-sm">
      <p>&copy; 2025 Red Flag Detector. All rights reserved.</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-gray-400">This tool is for informational purposes only. Please consult with a financial professional before taking action.</p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</div>